print("%d9f(:<:(::(register a new user))\n    ?: By what method is the user registration performed?\n    <= @by(:_:)\n        /: The registration is performed by a sequence of steps.\n    <- {steps}\n        ?: How are the steps composed as an ordered sequence?\n        <= &across\n            /: The steps are composed as an ordered sequence.\n        <- {step 1}\n            ?: How to judge whether the username exists in the database?\n            <= ::<username exists in database>\n                /: Check if the provided username already exists in the database\n            <- {provided username}\n                /: The username submitted by the user\n            <- {database}\n                /: The system's user records storage\n        <- {step 2}\n            ?: Under what condition is the error reported?\n             <= @if(<username exists in database>)\n                /: If the username exists, report an error\n            <- ::(report error)\n                /: Notify the user that the username is taken\n        <- {step 3}\n            ?: Under what condition is a new user account created?\n            <= @if!(<username exists in database>)\n                /: Otherwise, create a new user account\n            <- ::(create a new user account)\n                /: Create a new record for the user with the provided details)")